Defendant Kevin L Brockel in court with attorney Samuel W. Benedict.  Melissa Zilavy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Plea Colloquy.
Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 2.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Count 1 is dismissed and read in.   Statement by the victims.  

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:

9 months Jail (First 4 months Straight Time remaining Huber with Standard Release Conditions)  

Term of Probation: 2 Years

Conditions of Probation:
- AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Mental Health Evaluation and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Complete and Anger Management Course;
- Complete a Cognitive Thinking Course;
- Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
- No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- No  contact with Lawrence B. and his residence.  No violent contact with defendan'ts mother.  
- Maintain/Obtain full time employment.

Costs: $353.00 
DNA Surcharge:  $200.00
(To be paid at the rate of $50.00  per month commencing 9-1-15. Failure to pay  the Court orders 5 days Huber as contempt for non-compliance with Court Order).  As a condition of probation.

Condition Time: 90 days Huber NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS - Last 26 days Stayed to be used at the agent's discretion.  Credit - 64 days
